headline: Raymond James upgrades Genuine Parts on breakup value
summary: Investing.com -- Genuine Parts Company was upgraded to Strong Buy from Outperform at Raymond James, which set a $145 price target based on a sum-of-the-parts valuation following the planned separation of its Auto and Industrial businesses. Shares jumped 2% at $119 on Tuesday.

headline: 5 Revealing Analyst Questions From Genuine Parts’s Q4 Earnings Call
summary: Genuine Parts’ fourth quarter was marked by underperformance against Wall Street’s revenue and non-GAAP profit expectations, with the market responding negatively to the results. Management attributed the shortfall to weaker European market conditions and softer sales to independent owners in the U.S. NAPA business.
